User architectural critique: 'graph contamination problems · taxonomy
leakage · weak entity resolution · confidence inflation'.

THREE STRUCTURAL FIXES:

1. CONFIDENCE QUALITY CAP (no more 100% on 1 article)
   evidenceQualityCap(samples) gates confidence_pct by sample diversity:
     n=1 specialist source       →  60% cap
     n=1 generalist source       →  50% cap
     n=1 other                    →  35% cap
     n=2 same source              →  60-70% cap
     n=2 cross-source             →  70-80% cap
     n>=3 with 2+ distinct sources→  95-100% cap
     n>=3 single source           →  85% cap (still suspicious)
   Applied in readPersistentBottlenecks AFTER score-to-confidence calc.
   Also re-gates min_confidence using the EFFECTIVE (capped) confidence
   so n=1 dust doesn't slip through with falsely-high raw score.

2. CONTAMINATION MAP + PENALTY MULTIPLIER
   Counts how many distinct SystemNodes each ticker appears in (with
   live decay >=2).  buildContaminationMap() reads all 20 node buckets
   once per request, returns { TICKER: count }.

   contaminationMultiplier(count) returns [0.4..1.0]:
     1-3 nodes     1.0x (clean — sector-coherent)
     4-5 nodes     0.85x (mild dilution)
     6-7 nodes     0.65x (high dilution)
     8+ nodes      0.40x ('everything stock' — heavy penalty)

   Convexity score multiplied by this factor in deriveLayeredBeneficiaries.
   Net effect: a name like RELIANCE that appears in COMPUTE/MEMORY/ENERGY/
   RENEWABLE/MFG/LOGISTICS/CAPITAL nodes gets convexity halved or worse,
   so it surfaces lower than scarce-enabler midcaps with focused exposure.

   contamination_count exposed on every LayerTicker so UI can display
   '(in 8 nodes — likely theme dilution)' marker in a follow-up patch.

   Per-request cache (60s) so 20-key KV scan only runs once even across
   many bottleneck cards in a single endpoint call.

3. CACHE BUMP v35 → v36 so reclassified articles propagate.

Type-check clean.
